HEADWORD: Wildgrave
<hw>Wild"grave`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>wildgraf</ets> or D. <ets>wildgraaf</ets>. See <er>Wild</er>, and
cf. <er>Margrave</er>.]</ety> <def>A waldgrave, or head forest keeper.
See <er>Waldgrave</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>wildgrave</qex> winds his bugle horn.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
